cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.OS, cs.SE, cs.PF 

This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it discusses the need for effective resource utilisation monitoring and scheduling in Grid computing. It may also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category as it discusses monitoring per-process resource utilisation. Additionally, it may belong to the Operating Systems (cs.OS) sub-category as it discusses measuring and monitoring resource utilisation at the process level. It may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category as it presents a customisable tool for emulating observed utilisation models. Finally, it may belong to the Performance (cs.PF) sub-category as it discusses the need for more efficient Grid scheduling.
